# Stratelegy Insight — collaboration preferences

## Stack (do not assume Next.js)

- Vite + React SPA, Express API, MySQL, TanStack Query, shadcn/ui
- PBX integrates via SkySwitch (`server/services/skyswitch/`, `apiDocumentation.md`)
- Routes/permissions: `src/pages.config.js`, `shared/permissionRegistry.js`, `src/lib/navConfig.js`

## Secrets

- **Never** ask the user to paste passwords, API secrets, or SMTP credentials in chat
- Read from `.env` / `.env.example`; tell the user which variable is missing if auth fails
- If credentials were exposed in chat, recommend rotation — do not echo them back

## How to take tasks (prefer one scoped goal)

Use or ask for this shape when the request is vague or broad:

```
Goal: [one feature or bug]
URL: http://localhost:3000/...
Expected: ...
Actual: ...
Already tried: ...
Do NOT change: [files/areas]
```

- Decline or split "fix entire codebase / wire all APIs / every bug" into ordered steps
- After each change: state what to smoke-test (one URL + one action)

## Product bar (keep these defaults)

- SaaS structure: nav + permissions stay in sync with new pages/APIs
- Edit forms: load current data before PUT/update
- Remove dead pages from nav when features move (no orphan dropdowns)
- Filters only where list views need them — don't add noise

## Performance & debugging

- For slowness: identify route/handler/query first; suggest pagination or indexes before deleting unrelated UI
- Local dev: repo root, one API process; port conflicts → kill existing listener on 3000
- API calls: reasonable timeouts; stuck "loading" → trace server + network, not only spinner CSS

## Implementation style

- Minimal diff; match existing patterns in touched folders
- No commits unless the user asks
- Reuse `PbxFormSelect`, `pbxFormMappers`, permission gates — don't duplicate PBX form logic
